それを採用し、最終的なレスポンスを返す。 the consistent use of \"手順2\" throughout suggests \"手順1\" in the inner 3b list likely refers to the outer step 1 as well. Overall, the knowledge file seems clean with at most minor ambiguity concerns. Let me reconsider the section structure—the source file has an h1 title, h2 overview section, and h3 handler subsection, so I should verify how these map to the actual content organization. I'm double-checking for any subtle inaccuracies or missing details in the knowledge file. Looking at step 5 in section 3b, the source has a typo with a doubled verb phrase, but the knowledge file correctly simplified it to the proper form—that's fine. Everything checks out, so I'm confident the knowledge file is accurate and complete.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16005,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":16005,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b647734b-c899-4715-90d3-40fd8f56e287","uuid":"765d4b89-121a-48f7-afbc-7225cfb8b007"}
